<BaseLayout title="About | Arvind Puthucode" pageClass="garden-theme">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Arvind Puthucode</h2>
    <p>Founder building systems for signal detection and decision intelligence.</p>

    <p>
      I'm a builder interested in how people detect important signals in
      complex systems.
    </p>

    <p>
      I started my career as an engineer working on augmented analytics systems
      and large-scale data pipelines. Over time I became fascinated by a
      broader question: how do people notice the signals that actually matter
      for decisions?
    </p>

    <p>
      The internet produces enormous amounts of information every day: new
      research, product launches, regulatory changes, and market shifts. Most
      of these signals appear quietly across scattered sources long before they
      become obvious.
    </p>

    <p>Humans miss them constantly.</p>

    <p>
      That curiosity led me to start building systems that monitor the web and
      surface signals that help people make better decisions.
    </p>

    <p>
      In October 2025, I left my role to explore this idea more deeply through
      founder residencies and independent experiments.
    </p>

    <p>
      During the Lossfunk residency (Jan-Feb 2026), I started building
      ScoutFox, a system that monitors the web intelligently and surfaces
      signals that users should not miss.
    </p>

    <p>
      ScoutFox later won the OSS4AI February Hackathon and is currently being
      developed through the TinyFish accelerator program.
    </p>

    <p>
      My long-term focus is to build systems that surface the signals humans
      need to make better decisions.
    </p>

    <p>
      Outside of startups, I enjoy exploring unusual questions across science,
      intelligence systems, and technology.
    </p>
  </section>

